{
  "stem": "15686.2",
  "chunk_idx": 4,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 7.4,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "My brother and I shared a room, and we heard something that sounded like a crash and we also heard glass shatter.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And it woke us up about, oh, it must have been about 5:30 in the morning.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "But we didn't think much of it, because we lived in central Berlin, not for from the theater district, and there were some nightclubs there.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And there was a lot of traffic at night sometimes.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And sometimes there were some drunk drivers, and there were many accidents that happened-- automobile accidents-- and we thought somebody had crashed into a lamppost or into another car, and it was just that.",
      "word_count": 34
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So we just went back to sleep for another hour, and then when mother woke us up, she said to me go outside and buy some milk.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "In those days, you didn't have supermarkets.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] Milk was obtained two ways.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "It was either delivered to your door or you went to a little store called a creamery that sold milk and cheese.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Jews were not entitled to door-to-door delivery anymore, because the drivers refused to serve Jews.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "So fortunately, in the front of our apartment house on the street level, there were several little stores, and one of them was a creamery.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And my mother would every morning send-- we took turns, my brother and I-- send us out.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "So I went out it with a little pail that we had-- a little container just for the milk, and I went out to buy a quart of milk.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And when I came out to the street, I saw that there was another shop which belonged to a Jewish neighbor, who was a furrier, that his show window had been smashed.",
      "word_count": 32
    }
  ],
